==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punishable
<hw>Pun"ish*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>punissable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Deserving of, or liable to,
punishment; capable of being punished by law or right; -- said of person
or offenses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That time was, when to be a Protestant, to be a Christian, was by
law as <qex>punishable</qex> as to be a traitor.</q> <rj><qau>
Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pun"ish*a*ble*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punisher</ent>⟦br⟧
